      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Small, non-obvious damage could be caused by spider mites or thrips, which are tiny pests that are quite hard to see without a magnifying glass. Another possibility is fungal issues causing leaf spotting, which can look like small marks. If you suspect unseen pests, a strong jet of water can dislodge them, and for fungi, ensure good air circulation around your plants.",
